00:52:45,060 --> 00:52:46,820
(This is?)

1652
00:52:46,920 --> 00:52:47,520
What's this?

1653
00:52:47,720 --> 00:52:48,840
It's an imperial robe.

1654
00:52:49,960 --> 00:52:50,720
Seriously?

1655
00:52:50,720 --> 00:52:51,440
Is it?

1656
00:52:51,440 --> 00:52:51,920
Yes.

1657
00:52:54,260 --> 00:52:55,660
(Why aren't you kneeling
before your crown prince?)

1658
00:52:56,720 --> 00:52:58,440
Bring me my robe first.

1659
00:52:58,440 --> 00:52:59,940
(An order from Crown Prince Tui)

1660
00:53:01,880 --> 00:53:04,120
Bring the robe.

1661
00:53:05,540 --> 00:53:06,420
(Palace maid)

1662
00:53:11,500 --> 00:53:13,100
(Careful, Your Highness)

1663
00:53:13,120 --> 00:53:14,360
Princess of Kuang,

1664
00:53:15,320 --> 00:53:16,680
move your hand.

1665
00:53:17,160 --> 00:53:18,780
(How dare you challenge me?)
Open your hand.

1666
00:53:19,920 --> 00:53:21,320
I'll do it myself.

1667
00:53:21,920 --> 00:53:22,720
Here, let me open it for you.

1668
00:53:23,520 --> 00:53:24,760
Just wear it like this.

1669
00:53:24,760 --> 00:53:25,680
Like this.

1670
00:53:25,680 --> 00:53:26,720
You gotta do it like this.

1671
00:53:28,600 --> 00:53:28,880
Move!

1672
00:53:29,020 --> 00:53:29,980
(Oh)

1673
00:53:30,640 --> 00:53:32,920
He'd look good even in a burlap sack.

1674
00:53:33,860 --> 00:53:34,520
Come on.

1675
00:53:41,580 --> 00:53:42,740
(Wow)

1676
00:53:43,260 --> 00:53:45,020
(Wow)

1677
00:53:51,200 --> 00:53:53,300
You're before the crown prince.

1678
00:53:53,880 --> 00:53:55,400
(Way too into character)
Why aren't you kneeling?

1679
00:53:55,400 --> 00:53:56,360
He's already lying down.

1680
00:53:56,460 --> 00:53:57,780
(Fully prostrated)

1681
00:53:59,860 --> 00:54:01,620
(Who dares defy me?)

1682
00:54:02,040 --> 00:54:03,370
He looks insane.

1683
00:54:05,120 --> 00:54:06,880
What kind of crown prince are you?

1684
00:54:07,780 --> 00:54:08,580
(Why aren't you kneeling
before your crown prince?)

1685
00:54:09,080 --> 00:54:09,680
That's right.

1686
00:54:10,720 --> 00:54:13,720
I'm the crown prince of Tui.

1687
00:54:13,720 --> 00:54:15,360
Crown Prince Tui.

1688
00:54:16,120 --> 00:54:16,840
Yesterday, you thought

1689
00:54:16,840 --> 00:54:18,320
(Tui, He Ha, Crown Prince Tui)
I was some traveling con artist, right?

1690
00:54:18,320 --> 00:54:19,760
But my true identity

1691
00:54:19,760 --> 00:54:21,400
outranks everyone.

1692
00:54:22,180 --> 00:54:23,820
(He Ha, Crown Prince Tui)

1693
00:54:23,820 --> 00:54:26,860
(He Ha, Fortune-teller,
Crown Prince of Tui)

1694
00:54:27,080 --> 00:54:28,720
How do you outrank everyone?

1695
00:54:29,680 --> 00:54:30,600
What's so supreme about you?

1696
00:54:30,600 --> 00:54:32,120
The princess is just as important.

1697
00:54:32,120 --> 00:54:32,640
Right.

1698
00:54:32,640 --> 00:54:33,740
(Nothing outranks the princess)

1699
00:54:34,120 --> 00:54:37,760
Tui is the strongest
country in the world.

1700
00:54:37,760 --> 00:54:39,400
What's Kuang compared to us?

1701
00:54:39,400 --> 00:54:40,860
(Even wilder than Kuang)

1702
00:54:41,160 --> 00:54:42,920
Your country's full of our people.

1703
00:54:42,920 --> 00:54:44,280
The Jinyi Guard? Ours.

1704
00:54:44,280 --> 00:54:45,640
The chancellor? Ours.

1705
00:54:47,880 --> 00:54:50,080
Your country's entire Jinyi Guard is me.

1706
00:54:50,800 --> 00:54:52,680
Hold on.

1707
00:54:53,160 --> 00:54:54,520
Let me explain.

1708
00:54:55,040 --> 00:54:55,720
Okay.

1709
00:54:55,820 --> 00:54:58,700
(Do tell)

1710
00:54:59,320 --> 00:55:02,520
The year Tui, Li, and Kuang went to war,

1711
00:55:02,520 --> 00:55:03,280
I was born.

1712
00:55:03,340 --> 00:55:04,800
(He Ha's timeline)

1713
00:55:04,800 --> 00:55:05,980
(Year 239 : Born)
When I was five,

1714
00:55:06,000 --> 00:55:08,080
General Dong and I became good friends.

1715
00:55:08,100 --> 00:55:08,960
(Year 244: Became friends
with General Dong)

1716
00:55:08,960 --> 00:55:10,880
I really looked up to General Dong.

1717
00:55:10,880 --> 00:55:12,200
I told him,

1718
00:55:12,200 --> 00:55:13,680
"I want to be just like you".

1719
00:55:13,680 --> 00:55:15,560
"I want to become an incredible fighter"

1720
00:55:15,560 --> 00:55:17,520
"and conquer new lands with you".

1721
00:55:18,960 --> 00:55:20,720
But General Dong said something

1722
00:55:20,720 --> 00:55:22,160
that really shook me. He said,

1723
00:55:26,390 --> 00:55:28,460
(In my humble opinion,)

1724
00:55:28,460 --> 00:55:31,800
(Conquering new lands
will only leave people displaced)

1725
00:55:31,800 --> 00:55:33,210
(What we should do)

1726
00:55:33,210 --> 00:55:37,450
(Is hear the true voices of the people)

1727
00:55:37,450 --> 00:55:40,810
(Not kill loyal and righteous men)

1728
00:55:40,840 --> 00:55:42,260
(Influenced by his friend General Dong,)
That's what General Dong taught me.

1729
00:55:42,260 --> 00:55:43,120
(He Ha vowed to protect peace)

1730
00:55:43,120 --> 00:55:44,880
What vision.

1731
00:55:44,880 --> 00:55:46,120
You don't even remember
saying that, do you?

1732
00:55:46,580 --> 00:55:47,820
(It's all in my heart)

1733
00:55:47,840 --> 00:55:50,320
Later, General Dong
joined the Longdong Army

1734
00:55:50,320 --> 00:55:51,200
and enlisted.

1735
00:55:51,360 --> 00:55:52,280
So we parted ways.

1736
00:55:52,280 --> 00:55:53,160
But before he left,

1737
00:55:53,160 --> 00:55:54,640
he gave me a flute.

1738
00:55:54,640 --> 00:55:55,000
Okay.

1739
00:55:55,640 --> 00:55:57,720
It's the flute I'm holding.

1740
00:55:57,820 --> 00:55:59,080
(The piccolo General Dong gave He Ha)

1741
00:55:59,080 --> 00:56:00,200
General Dong told me,

1742
00:56:00,200 --> 00:56:02,360
"Whenever you're in trouble,"

1743
00:56:02,480 --> 00:56:04,160
"just blow this flute,"

1744
00:56:04,160 --> 00:56:06,160
"and I'll appear by your side".

1745
00:56:06,220 --> 00:56:08,980
(He Ha can summon General Dong
by blowing the piccolo)

1746
00:56:09,000 --> 00:56:10,600
Now I'm going

1747
00:56:10,600 --> 00:56:12,560
to summon General Dong

1748
00:56:12,560 --> 00:56:14,680
to teach you a lesson.

1749
00:56:24,420 --> 00:56:26,420
(Ning Waver starts moving)

1750
00:56:37,820 --> 00:56:39,020
(Lung capacity maxed out)

1751
00:56:41,080 --> 00:56:42,560
Your Highness, hop on.

1752
00:56:42,560 --> 00:56:45,220
(Childhood best friends
reunited after sixteen years)

1753
00:56:52,160 --> 00:56:52,400
Okay.

1754
00:56:54,040 --> 00:56:54,840
Okay.

1755
00:56:54,840 --> 00:56:56,500
(A childhood promise between ruler
and subject, still kept years later)

1756
00:56:57,280 --> 00:56:58,080
Nice.

1757
00:56:58,500 --> 00:56:59,660
(Ah)

1758
00:56:59,740 --> 00:57:00,740
(Oh)

1759
00:57:00,780 --> 00:57:01,740
(Wow)

1760
00:57:03,120 --> 00:57:03,520
Right.

1761
00:57:03,760 --> 00:57:05,160
The crown prince has bad knees.

1762
00:57:05,300 --> 00:57:08,020
(Wow)

1763
00:57:08,500 --> 00:57:09,940
(Oh)

1764
00:57:10,380 --> 00:57:11,040
(Oh)

1765
00:57:11,040 --> 00:57:11,440
Right.

1766
00:57:11,440 --> 00:57:12,040
Just like that.

1767
00:57:13,340 --> 00:57:16,580
(Wow)

1768
00:57:16,880 --> 00:57:17,240
Alright.

1769
00:57:17,240 --> 00:57:17,960
What's wrong with you?

1770
00:57:17,960 --> 00:57:18,800
This isn't bad either.

1771
00:57:18,860 --> 00:57:20,200
(Getting fed by everyone)

1772
00:57:20,200 --> 00:57:21,000
Honestly,

1773
00:57:21,000 --> 00:57:22,800
I barely remember him
being the crown prince.

1774
00:57:23,600 --> 00:57:24,040
You forgot your roots.

1775
00:57:25,120 --> 00:57:26,680
No, it's because he was so young.

1776
00:57:26,880 --> 00:57:27,480
He was only five.

1777
00:57:27,480 --> 00:57:28,520
When I was eight,

1778
00:57:28,520 --> 00:57:29,680
I was sent to the palace

1779
00:57:29,680 --> 00:57:30,760
as the crown prince's study companion,

1780
00:57:30,760 --> 00:57:31,960
and I taught him martial arts.

1781
00:57:31,960 --> 00:57:32,680
(Ning Waver was He Ha's study companion)

1782
00:57:32,680 --> 00:57:33,960
(And taught him martial arts)
I also told him,

1783
00:57:33,960 --> 00:57:35,640
"One day, you must be a good emperor".

1784
00:57:35,640 --> 00:57:38,440
For all the people under heaven,

1785
00:57:38,440 --> 00:57:42,300
you must become a truly upstanding man.

1786
00:57:42,520 --> 00:57:43,880
But the real upstanding man

1787
00:57:43,880 --> 00:57:45,480
is someone else.

1788
00:57:46,180 --> 00:57:47,740
(That would be me)

1789
00:57:47,760 --> 00:57:48,880
Ning, I'm right here.

1790
00:57:51,080 --> 00:57:52,480
Okay, fair.

1791
00:57:52,640 --> 00:57:53,240
Just a coincidence, right?

1792
00:57:55,160 --> 00:57:56,520
Well? What do you think?

1793
00:57:56,520 --> 00:57:57,960
The two of us together

1794
00:57:58,360 --> 00:57:59,240
outrank you guys

1795
00:57:59,960 --> 00:58:00,680
by a lot, right?

1796
00:58:03,160 --> 00:58:04,040
Rank doesn't matter, Your Highness.

1797
00:58:04,040 --> 00:58:04,760
I...

1798
00:58:05,000 --> 00:58:06,800
(Sworn to protect the princess)
I'll die for... I...

1799
00:58:07,480 --> 00:58:07,760
Forget it.

1800
00:58:07,760 --> 00:58:08,680
These two are way too strong.

1801
00:58:08,680 --> 00:58:09,080
True.

1802
00:58:09,080 --> 00:58:10,600
(Level up first)

1803
00:58:10,600 --> 00:58:11,560
Look.

1804
00:58:11,560 --> 00:58:14,240
General Dong left me this line.

1805
00:58:14,240 --> 00:58:15,520
Now this is what you call vision.

1806
00:58:17,240 --> 00:58:18,480
End war.

1807
00:58:18,940 --> 00:58:19,820
(Crown Prince of Tui
has questionable eyesight)

1808
00:58:21,880 --> 00:58:26,120
End war, and spill no innocent blood.

1809
00:58:26,120 --> 00:58:30,640
I wield my staff only
to guard the eternal light.

1810
00:58:33,180 --> 00:58:34,900
(Vision)

1811
00:58:34,920 --> 00:58:37,160
(Goddess of Peace is delighted)
Good. Well said.

1812
00:58:39,000 --> 00:58:40,860
(Sword drawn)
Good. Well said.

1813
00:58:41,380 --> 00:58:42,220
(Anything to make the princess happy)

1814
00:58:42,320 --> 00:58:43,160
Okay.

1815
00:58:43,160 --> 00:58:45,000
You're not thinking big enough!

1816
00:58:46,760 --> 00:58:48,640
Don't pick on me just
because I'm uneducated.

1817
00:58:50,600 --> 00:58:52,600
I just didn't get much schooling.

1818
00:58:53,000 --> 00:58:54,440
But

1819
00:58:54,440 --> 00:58:56,120
I was desperate to protect the princess.

1820
00:58:56,120 --> 00:58:57,920
(Desperate means urgent)
I was desperately urgent.

1821
00:58:57,920 --> 00:59:00,400
(A little more cultured)
I'd die for her anytime, anywhere.

1822
00:59:01,520 --> 00:59:02,720
You little punk.

1823
00:59:02,720 --> 00:59:03,840
You've got all that martial arts skill,

1824
00:59:03,840 --> 00:59:05,200
but no brains.

1825
00:59:05,200 --> 00:59:06,200
That's fine.

1826
00:59:06,200 --> 00:59:07,520
I'm a blade.

1827
00:59:07,520 --> 00:59:09,080
A blade doesn't need brains.

1828
00:59:09,080 --> 00:59:11,440
It just needs to be sharp enough.

1829
00:59:11,440 --> 00:59:12,920
Sharp enough.

1830
00:59:15,220 --> 00:59:16,620
(Shook. Delicious)

1831
00:59:16,880 --> 00:59:17,640
You're the muscle.

1832
00:59:17,640 --> 00:59:19,160
She's the brains.

1833
00:59:20,120 --> 00:59:20,400
Right.

1834
00:59:20,400 --> 00:59:22,460
(The queen and her loyal guard)

1835
00:59:23,390 --> 00:59:24,990
I grew up relying on others.

1836
00:59:25,520 --> 00:59:27,120
But after everything that's happened,

1837
00:59:27,120 --> 00:59:29,000
I suddenly came across someone.

1838
00:59:30,400 --> 00:59:31,360
The Crown Prince of Li.

1839
00:59:31,360 --> 00:59:33,120
He's the one I've hated for years.

1840
00:59:33,120 --> 00:59:34,760
(The one he hates)

1841
00:59:34,760 --> 00:59:37,400
We've been exchanging letters for years.

1842
00:59:37,820 --> 00:59:38,960
(Why did longtime friends
become enemies?)

1843
00:59:38,960 --> 00:59:42,160
I noticed he has a few little habits

1844
00:59:42,160 --> 00:59:43,440
that are just like
the Crown Prince of Li's.

1845
00:59:43,440 --> 00:59:44,200
What's that got to do with you?

1846
00:59:44,220 --> 00:59:46,020
(Crown Prince of Li)?

1847
00:59:46,160 --> 00:59:48,720
The way he eats blueberries

1848
00:59:48,720 --> 00:59:49,800
is exactly like the Crown Prince of Li's

1849
00:59:49,800 --> 00:59:51,520
habit when he used

1850
00:59:51,520 --> 00:59:52,760
to write to me.

1851
00:59:53,380 --> 00:59:56,260
(Crown Prince of Li loves
blueberries. Could Ding Pillar be him?)

1852
00:59:56,800 --> 00:59:58,040
Blueberries?

1853
00:59:58,280 --> 00:59:59,680
The Blueberry Prince.

1854
01:00:00,240 --> 01:00:01,520
I got really curious,

1855
01:00:01,520 --> 01:00:02,400
so I went

1856
01:00:03,200 --> 01:00:05,760
to Ding Pillar's room

1857
01:00:05,760 --> 01:00:07,280
to investigate.

1858
01:00:07,560 --> 01:00:09,040
What did you find?

1859
01:00:10,880 --> 01:00:12,440
I found

1860
01:00:12,440 --> 01:00:14,520
a rubbing of the Crown Prince
of Li in his room.

1861
01:00:14,980 --> 01:00:19,300
(Why does Ding Pillar have a rubbing
of the Crown Prince of Li?)

1862
01:00:19,320 --> 01:00:20,200
Any other clues?

1863
01:00:20,200 --> 01:00:21,120
Let's take a look.

1864
01:00:21,220 --> 01:00:22,200
(He Ha's package)

1865
01:00:22,200 --> 01:00:23,480
How do we piece this together?

1866
01:00:23,480 --> 01:00:25,400
Do we actually have
to put this together? No way.

1867
01:00:25,460 --> 01:00:27,940
(Letter fragments)

1868
01:00:27,960 --> 01:00:29,280
Don't we have a card for this?

1869
01:00:29,280 --> 01:00:29,880
A Restore Card.

1870
01:00:29,880 --> 01:00:30,600
Restore Card.

1871
01:00:30,620 --> 01:00:33,260
(Restore Card holder)

1872
01:00:37,360 --> 01:00:40,000
Let's use the Restore Card.

1873
01:00:40,000 --> 01:00:42,900
(Restore Card)

1874
01:00:47,160 --> 01:00:50,000
The Tale of the Ugly Man
and the Weird Prince.

1875
01:00:50,060 --> 01:00:52,300
(A suspicious biography
found in He Ha's package)

1876
01:00:52,560 --> 01:00:54,720
(The Ugly Man and Weird Prince)
Two crown princes

1877
01:00:54,720 --> 01:00:57,800
both reject the beautiful
Princess of Kuang.

1878
01:00:57,800 --> 01:00:59,360
Princess, run!

1879
01:00:59,360 --> 01:01:02,320
These two are nothing but red flags.

1880
01:01:02,380 --> 01:01:05,820
(Crown Princes of Tui and Li are
both linked to the Princess of Kuang)

1881
01:01:07,860 --> 01:01:10,000
One is hideously ugly.

1882
01:01:11,540 --> 01:01:13,550
One is weird and antisocial.

1883
01:01:14,720 --> 01:01:16,340
One is the Crown Prince of Tui.

1884
01:01:16,340 --> 01:01:18,250
One is the Crown Prince of Li.

1885
01:01:18,250 --> 01:01:20,010
Ugly and weird clash.

1886
01:01:20,010 --> 01:01:21,750
Natural enemies.

1887
01:01:21,860 --> 01:01:23,020
(Now that's some juicy gossip)

1888
01:01:23,100 --> 01:01:26,020
(Crown Princes of Tui
and Li are natural enemies)

1889
01:01:26,020 --> 01:01:27,770
But at the peace talks,

1890
01:01:27,770 --> 01:01:31,010
it wasn't his land that he coveted.

1891
01:01:31,300 --> 01:01:32,620
(Then what did he want?)

1892
01:01:32,620 --> 01:01:34,240
Five years.

1893
01:01:34,240 --> 01:01:36,750
4,250 letters.

1894
01:01:36,750 --> 01:01:38,710
Every single one ended

1895
01:01:38,710 --> 01:01:39,520
with "together".

1896
01:01:39,520 --> 01:01:41,100
Some say "together"

1897
01:01:41,100 --> 01:01:44,030
means fighting to the death

1898
01:01:44,030 --> 01:01:45,460
and never reconciling.

1899
01:01:45,460 --> 01:01:46,500
Others say

1900
01:01:46,500 --> 01:01:47,950
it's two kindred spirits

1901
01:01:47,950 --> 01:01:51,550
in perfect harmony.

1902
01:01:51,550 --> 01:01:53,300
Whatever kind of "together" it is,

1903
01:01:53,300 --> 01:01:55,570
their taste is definitely
a perfect match.

1904
01:01:55,570 --> 01:01:59,190
One ugly, one weird.
They must both be blind.

1905
01:01:59,190 --> 01:02:02,770
They can't see that
the Princess of Kuang is gorgeous.

1906
01:02:02,770 --> 01:02:06,940
They're more like a dump
and a sewer struck by lightning.

1907
01:02:07,000 --> 01:02:07,880
Does it really say that?

1908
01:02:07,880 --> 01:02:08,580
She made that up.

1909
01:02:08,580 --> 01:02:09,880
(Saw right through her)
She made that up, didn't she?

1910
01:02:09,980 --> 01:02:12,620
(Don't I deserve a name?)

1911
01:02:12,640 --> 01:02:15,820
Author: Princess of Kuang.

1912
01:02:15,820 --> 01:02:16,540
(I'm the page number)

1913
01:02:16,540 --> 01:02:17,160
(The Tale of the Ugly Man and the
Weird Prince was written by Jin Thrifty)

1914
01:02:17,160 --> 01:02:17,800
You wrote this?

1915
01:02:17,800 --> 01:02:18,360
Yeah.

1916
01:02:18,840 --> 01:02:21,240
The note says, "Absurd,
despicable little man".

1917
01:02:21,240 --> 01:02:22,040
"Not worthy at all".

1918
01:02:22,040 --> 01:02:23,560
"Only eight words
in this whole thing are right".

1919
01:02:23,800 --> 01:02:24,840
"Natural enemies".

1920
01:02:24,840 --> 01:02:26,360
"Never reconcile, even in death".

1921
